==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monureid
<hw>Mon*u"re*id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mon-</ets> +
<ets>ureid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of a series of
complex nitrogenous substances regarded as derived from one molecule of
urea; <as>as, alloxan is a <ex>monureid</ex></as>.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>monureide</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moo</ent>⟦br⟧
